fragment_downloaded_cb({"url": "gtkcellareacontext.html#page-description", "fragment": "The GtkCellAreaContext object is created by a given GtkCellArea implementation via its do_create_context virtual method and is used to store cell sizes and alignments for a series of GtkTreeModel rows that are requested and rendered in the same context. \nGtkCellLayout widgets can create any number of contexts in which to request and render groups of data rows. However it s important that the same context which was used to request sizes for a given GtkTreeModel row also be used for the same row when calling other GtkCellArea APIs such as gtk_cell_area_render and gtk_cell_area_event. \n"});